    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="263"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the British Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d263fn1">For the discussion of this paper by the Combined
                        Chiefs of Staff at their 174th Meeting, September 14, 1944, see <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_331">p. 331</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 452/26</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quebec</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-11">11 September
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">British Participation in the War Against Japan</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>We have seen the views of the United States Chiefs of Staff in <gloss
                            target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 452/25<note n="2" xml:id="d263fn2">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_257">p. 257</ref>.</note>
                        concerning British participation in the Pacific in the war against Japan,
                        and we note that no mention is made of the employment of the British Fleet
                        in the main operations against Japan, for which we expressed a preference in
                            <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 452/18.<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d263fn3">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_244">p. 244</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In view of the important political considerations involved, we request a
                        formal expression of the views of the United States Chiefs of Staff on our
                        first preference—namely, the employment of the Fleet in the main operations
                        against Japan.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
